def: The lapwing; -- called also teewheep. [Prov. Eng.]
The quality or state of being imponderable; imponderableness.
pertaining to the sacculus and cochlea of the ear.
Any plant of the genus Lechea, low North American herbs withbranching stems, and very small and abundant leaves and flowers.
A narrow band or fillet; a part of a head-dress.Around the edge of this cap was a stiff bandeau of leather. Sir W.Scott.
That which is opaque; opacity. Young.
To name the current price of.
To plaster over; to cover or smear thickly; to bedaub.Beplastered with rouge. Goldsmith.
Of or pertaining to Complutum (now Alcala de Henares) a citynear Madrid; as, the Complutensian Bible.
